Content / data
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The bundled data in data/*.json may contain real-world criminal case information, court records, legal references, public records, and information compiled from reputable and verifiable sources.

Avow is a criminal case documentation and legal research platform. Published case records are intended for research, educational, archival, and public-interest purposes. Avow aims to document criminal cases using publicly available records, judicial decisions, official documents, and other reliable sources.

Where individuals are identified as offenders, such references are based on court judgments, official legal determinations, or authoritative public records available at the time of publication. Information may be updated, corrected, or supplemented as new official records or judicial decisions become available.

The Apache License 2.0 applies solely to the software components of Avow, including its source code, styles, assets, and tooling. The license does not govern the factual content of case records or source materials.

